OL,3,CFamily of runner killed by electricity
OL,4,Ccable make statement
OL,6,F"Inspections and patrols that could
OL,7,Fhave identified the danger were not
OL,8,Fcarried out, and the policy of relying
OL,9,Fon the public to report hazardous
OL,10,Fpower lines in rural areas proved to
OL,11,Fbe fatally flawed.
OL,13,F"What is also alarming to us is that
OL,14,Fthe fatal risk remains ever-present
OL,15,Ftoday. While Electricity North West
OL,16,FLtd is now working to replace
OL,17,Fdefective insulators and introduce new
OL,18,FLinesight LINESIGHT technology to
OL,19,Fimprove safety, these measures will
OL,20,Ftake years to fully implement."
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G3/7
