OL,4,Ccable make statement
OL,6,FDuring the inquest Paul Killilea, from
OL,7,FElectricity North West, told the
OL,8,Finquest there was an unprecedented
OL,9,Fsituation involving simultaneous
OL,10,Ffaults with one of their poles, which
OL,11,Fled to the cable dropping low enough
OL,12,Fto make contact with Mr Oates.
OL,14,FJeffery Fisher from the Health and
OL,15,FSafety Executive, meanwhile, told the
OL,16,FCoroner the company acted
OL,17,Fappropriately and said the incident
OL,18,Fwas "a very unique set of
OL,19,Fcircumstances, but unlikely, and
OL,20,Funforeseeable".
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G6/7
